Global Electric Shavers Market Insights
Electric Shavers Market size was valued at USD 20.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 30.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Electric Shavers Market Overview
The global electric shavers market is valued at approximately USD 20 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 30 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% during the forecast period. This growth is attributed to rising consumer demand for personal grooming products, coupled with technological advancements in electric shaving devices. Consumers are increasingly opting for electric shavers due to their convenience, efficiency, and time-saving features. In particular, the rise in disposable incomes, along with growing awareness of personal grooming, is expected to continue fueling market expansion. The demand is also significantly driven by innovation in product design and features, such as cordless operation, wet and dry shaving options, and longer battery life.

